    "narrative": "The centerpiece of today\u2019s lineup is **Jazz Chisholm Jr.**, our clear top play with a 75.32 score. Facing Leiter, **Jazz Chisholm Jr.** benefits significantly from a favorable platoon advantage and a high-yield matchup against a slow-delivery pitcher, which maximizes his elite speed profile for potential stolen bases. **Seiya Suzuki** also warrants strong consideration (64.91) as he faces a generous 5.43 xERA from V\u00e1squez. While the park factors for **Seiya Suzuki** are slightly negative, the projected SP skill gap provides enough cushion to make him a high-efficiency start in our pursuit of R and RBI.\n\nWe are navigating a narrow margin with **Jose Caballero** (53.07) and **Alex Freeland** (50.41), both of whom are hindered by the 9-hole anchor in the batting order. While **Jose Caballero** remains a tactical start due to the 94% stolen base opportunity against Leiter, his score is suppressed by a negative platoon shift. Similarly, **Trevor Story** (55.32) is a marginal play today; though he gains a 4% efficiency boost from the slow delivery of Cease, the 3.58 xERA of his opponent remains a significant hurdle. **Josh Naylor** rounds out our starts at 57.90; despite the tough look against Prielipp, his role in the heart of the order and power profile keep him just above our bench threshold.\n\nRegarding our bench, the lack of active games for high-ceiling speedsters like **Corbin Carroll**, **James Wood**, **Mickey Moniak**, and **Brice Turang** has effectively forced our hand today. Had they been active, **Brice Turang** likely would have supplanted **Alex Freeland** due to the scarcity of speed, but with the current roster constraints, we are leaning heavily on **Jazz Chisholm Jr.** to anchor the stolen base category. We remain vigilant regarding the lineup status for **Josh Naylor**; should he be shifted down the order or benched by the team, we lack a direct high-efficiency pivot, which could force us to look toward the reserve utility depth of **Zach McKinstry** or **Max Muncy** to mitigate a potential cap-wasting start.",
